# Day 20 – AWS RDS Basics & Troubleshooting

## Goal
Learn how to set up, connect, and troubleshoot RDS databases.

## Steps
- Created RDS instance (MySQL).
- Configured security group for DB port.
- Connected using endpoint, port, and credentials.
- Troubleshot common issues (connection, timeout, permissions).
- Enabled automated backups and tested restore.

## Lessons Learned
- Security groups control DB access.
- Endpoint + port + credentials are required for connection.
- Performance Insights helps with slow queries.
- Snapshots ensure recovery in case of failure.

